{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01PZJ5Edn7udTFGgM4VTqZ5h","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Ai4VDjM3FZYU7w14aEHg57","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd /tmp/fdb-pack6-F0-thread-affine-readers-20260504T115216Z && git add src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/perf_gates.rs src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/reader_pool.rs && git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nrefactor(F0): thread-affine reader worker pool\n\nReplace ReaderPool::Mutex<Vec<Connection>> + Condvar borrow/release\nwith 8 long-lived worker threads, each owning exactly one read-only\nSQLite Connection for its lifetime. Engine::search dispatches a\nReaderRequest over a per-worker bounded channel using a lock-free\nAtomicUsize round-robin counter; no global mutex on the hot path.\nConnections never cross thread boundaries after startup. Worker\nshutdown joins all threads and drops connections before\nprofile_contexts is freed.\n\nAdds tests/reader_pool.rs covering shutdown integrity, drop without\nexplicit close, and a routing/concurrency stress that asserts every\nsearch lands on a worker exactly once. AC-017 / AC-018 / AC-020\n(short-mode) and the rest of the workspace stay green.\n\nPack 6 F.0 — closes the borrow/release and cross-thread handoff\nsuspects identified by Pack 5 final synthesis.\nEOF\n)\"","description":"Commit F.0"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":558,"cache_read_input_tokens":107029,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":558},"output_tokens":68,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"62439105-342d-48a7-9848-2f7271298010","uuid":"29d24d1c-da4a-49c3-a917-b398cb64f484"}
